MyLife and its service providers collect two main types of information through the Services: Personal Information and Other Information.

“Personal Information” refers to information that can be used to contact you or identify you as a particular individual. The specific kinds of Personal Information we collect through the Services typically depend on the exact nature of our relationship with you, but might include:

Full name;
Address (e.g., postal, billing, shipping, etc.);
Telephone number including cell number;
Fax number;
E-mail address;
Date of birth;
Payment information (e.g., credit or debit card number, expiration date, other financial account details, etc.);
User ID, login name, screen name, nickname, or handle and password;
Social media accounts and/or IDs;
Likeness and physical characteristics (e.g., profile picture, eye and hair color, height, etc.); and
vDetails regarding background or preferences (e.g., interests, nicknames, favorite quote, etc.);
IP Address;
School, workplace and job position;
Criminal record

“Other Information” refers to any information that does not reveal your specific identity or directly relate to you as an individual. We collect a number of different types of Other Information through the Services, such as:

Browser and device information (e.g., browser/device type, UDID, geographic location, etc.);
Information collected through cookies, pixel tags, and other tracking technologies;
Demographic and other similar information you provide (e.g., gender, ethnicity, relationship status, etc.); and
Aggregated or otherwise de-identified information.

MyLife uses the information we collect about you through the Services (including Personal Information) in order to, among other things:

Confirm and complete the transactions you request;
Operate, monitor, manage, improve, and expand the Services and/or our business activities;
Provide you with customer service support and other requested information or services;
Respond to your inquiries and resolve your problems or disputes;
Develop, enhance, and market our products and services or the products and services of third parties;
Communicate with you about your interactions with the Services and your MyLife account;
Provide you with promotional offers, administrative materials, and other related content (including interest-based advertising);
Personalize your content and experiences on the Services;
Allow you to participate in sweepstakes, contests, or promotions upon your request (note that these activities may be sponsored by third parties and additional rules or disclosures may apply to the treatment of your Personal Information — we encourage you to carefully read the terms and conditions applicable to any sweepstakes, contests, or promotions prior to enrolling);
Facilitate social sharing, messaging, or other similar functionalities on the Services;
Protect the rights or property of MyLife or third parties (including through the enforcement of this Policy, the User Agreement, and other applicable agreements and policies); and
Comply with legal or other regulatory requirements.

We may also use your Personal Information for other purposes when you provide us with prior consent to use your information in such a manner. For example, we may use Personal Information in accordance with disclosures made available to you when you submit that information through the Services, or as otherwise disclosed in this Policy.

Please note that unless expressly stated herein, MyLife may use and disclose Other Information for any purposes allowed by applicable laws and regulations. Under certain circumstances we may combine Other Information (e.g., a Member's geographical location) with Personal Information (e.g., the Member's name). If we do so, MyLife will treat the combined information as Personal Information for as long as it is remains combined and identifies you as a particular individual.
